@NODE E.intro "Introduction"
@PREV MAIN

@{b}MakeAminetTree@{ub} (short @{b}MAT@{ub}) makes the directory-structure of Aminet from the file
"TREE" ("ftp://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/aminet/TREE").
Alternatively every directory gets an english comment.

@{b}MAT@{ub} should make work easier to manage and find archives fast, which are downloaded
from Aminet. With @{b}MAT@{ub} and the file "TREE" you make all directories of Aminet, sort the
archives in and can find them easy with the aid of an INDEX-file. Programs, which
generates INDEX-files, are available from Aminet.

If @{b}MAT@{ub} is started a second time with the same destination-directory but a newer file
"TREE", then allready existing directories will be preserved with their contents and new
directories will be added.
@ENDNODE

